gomodel:SYNGO_4818  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: confocal immunofluorescence imagings showed auditory inner hair cells (IHC) lack Munc13 and CAPS priming factors.\n\nFigure 4a: co-staining of Otoferlin (OTOF) and CtBP2 showed Otoferlin is enriched in IHC ribbon synapse active zones.\n\nFigure 4b-g: electron tomography of IHC synapses showed vesicular tethers at active zones observed in wildtype condition were abolished in otoferlin-deficient IHCs. Otoferlin appears to be required to form short tethers (<10nm) between vesicles and active zone membranes.\n\nIt remains unclear whether Otoferlin is a tether constituent and, if so, homophilic interactions of Otoferlin molecules localized to vesicular and plasma membranes are involved.. Experimental description: M&M: \"otoferlin-KO (Otof-KO; Reisinger et al., 2011) mice of either sex were used to prepare organotypic cultures of the organ of Corti as described previously (Nouvian et al., 2011; Reisinger et al., 2011).\"\n\nantibody:\nmouse or rabbit anti-otoferlin antibodies (Abcam/Synaptic Systems)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4818" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

